<item>
            <title>[MAHOUT-411] Configurable reload interval in FileDataModel</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-411</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Patch to enable the following usecase:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;all preferences are kept in a text file and loaded via a FileDataModel&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;at some point in time the text file is completely overwritten with more recent preferences&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;an explicit refresh() on the FileDataModel is called&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;With the current FileDataModel, one could not see the new preferences as it would only have refreshed the whole file if that was modified more than one minute ago. And I don&apos;t want to wait that long to trigger the explicit refresh.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch makes the interval configurable with keeping the old interval length as default.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hope I understood the intention of the refreshing mechanism right.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
